description._content: Description: Part of the Native Government Station on Beru Island, in the Southern Gilberts. Location: Beru Island, Southern Gilberts, Kiribati ------------------------------------------------------ Description: A view of the District Officer's house on Beru Island, the administrative headquarters for the Southern Gilberts District. The house is built entirely of native materials, without a single nail. Location: Beru Island, Southern Gilberts, Kiribati ------------------------------------------------------ Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/642. This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons. Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location.
